Chocolate Beet Cake
  --@bdylanhollis

Cake:
15 oz can pickled beets
1/2 c vegetable oil
1 1/2 c sugar
1 tsp vanilla
3 eggs
2 c flour
1/3 c cocoa powder
1 tsp baking soda
pinch salt

Preheat oven to 375F; butter & flour baking vessel. Blend beets until smooth (juice and all). In a bowl add oil, sugar, vanilla, and eggs; whisk together. Add beets and whisk until thoroughly combined. In another bowl add the flour, cocoa powder, baking soda, and salt; stir/whisk to combine. Pour the dry ingredients into wet and fold until just combined. Pour into prepped baking vessel and bake ~50 min. Let cool before popping out of vessel.

Ganache:
1/2 c cream
4 oz chocolate

Put all ingredients into a pot and warm over very low heat until chcolate has melted and everything is smooth. Pour over cake and serve.


Notes: he used something akin to a bundt pan for baking
